PyCitySchools Analysis

Students at Charter Schools score much higher on their math and reading tests than students at District Schools. The Charter School students have a 90% Overall Passing Rate compared with the Distrcit School students at only 54%.

Students at large schools (2000-5000 students) scored significantly lower on their math and reading tests than students at medium schools (1000-2000 students) and small schools (<1000). Large school students had an Overall Passing rate at 58% compared to students at medium and small schools at 90%.

According to this data, increased spending per student doesn't mean higher test scores.  The schools with the highest amount spent per student ($645-$675) had the lowest Overall Passing Rate at 53%, compared to the lower spending schools at 63%-90%.

